President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring April 16-24, 2016, as National Park Week. The proclamation highlights the importance of national parks in allowing people to connect with history, nature, and wildlife. During National Park Week, the National Park Service will offer free admission to encourage more people to explore the natural beauty of the country. The proclamation also mentions initiatives such as the "Find Your Park" campaign and the "Every Kid in a Park" initiative, which aim to encourage Americans, especially young people, to visit and appreciate national parks. President Obama emphasizes the need to protect and preserve these parks for future generations and mentions his efforts in expanding public land and combating climate change. The proclamation calls on Americans to participate in various activities in national parks and to promote environmental stewardship.